Leonard Shlain, &quot;Leonardo's Brain: Understanding Da Vinci's Creative Genius&quot;

ISBN: 1493003356 | 2014 | EPUB | 240 pages | 11 MB


Best-selling author Leonard Shlain explores the life, art, and mind of Leonardo da Vinci, seeking to explain his singularity by looking at his achievements in art, science, psychology, and military strategy and then employing state of the art left-right brain scientific research to explain his universal genius. Shlain shows that no other person in human history has excelled in so many different areas as da Vinci and he peels back the layers to explore the how and the why.Shlain asserts that Leonardo's genius came from a unique creative ability that allowed him to understand and excel in a wide range of fields
